                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Mercantile Liby. March 5&#44; 1888.<lb/>
                Rev. Dr. Morais&#44; Philad<hi rend="sup">a</hi>.<lb/>
                Dear Sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Permit me to inquire of<lb/> you whether the statement is cor&#45;<lb/>rect&#44; which is handed about&#44; in<lb/> certain publications&#44; that &#34;from time<lb/> immemorial&#34; Israelites have been<lb/> at liberty to use&#44; in Passover obser&#45;<lb/>vances&#44; either the <hi rend="underline">fermented</hi> or the<lb/> <hi rend="underline">unfermented</hi> juice of the grape&#44; as<lb/> they chose.  I am desirous of<lb/> knowing what is historical on<lb/> this point.<lb/></p>
            <p>Are your families <hi rend="underline">now</hi> instructed<lb/> to use the raisin wine without any<lb/> fermentation&#44; if they please&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>At present the &#34;two&#45;kinds&#45;of&#45;wine&#34;<lb/> discussion has died away in this part<lb/> of the country&#59; but in remote districts<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>it rages considerably&#44; and the<lb/> organ of the Nat. Temp. Soc. is<lb/> still giving unverified statements.<lb/></p>
            <p>The <hi rend="underline">two&#45;wine</hi> writers are not<lb/> scholars&#44; and they pick up whatever<lb/> they can find in shallow books.  Our<lb/> good scholars&#45;&#45;without exception&#44;<lb/> so far as I know&#45;&#45;reject what is<lb/> called &#34;the two&#45;wine theory.&#34;  They<lb/> do not believe that Ps. civ&#58; 15 re&#45;<lb/>fers to unfermented grape&#45;juice.<lb/></p>
            <p>I find it as difficult to per&#45;<lb/>suade ordinary Temp. writers to be<lb/> careful and accurate&#44; as it is to<lb/> persuade a good many men not to<lb/> guzzle <sic>whisky</sic>.<lb/></p>
            <p>I wish that some student of<lb/> Hebrew would write an elaborate<lb/> monograph&#45;&#45;say for the <hi rend="underline">Biblio&#45;<lb/> theca Sacra</hi>&#45;&#45;on the world <hi rend="underline">Tirosh</hi>.<lb/>  I have suggested this to several of<lb/> them&#44; but don&#39;t know as I can get<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>any one at it.  Dr. Hovey has said&#44;<lb/> in one of his admirable articles&#44; that<lb/> he does not feel entirely satisfied as<lb/> to this word.  The exposition should&#44;<lb/> of course&#44; take in the post&#45;Biblical<lb/> writings in Hebrew.<lb/></p>
            <p>I am respectfully<lb/>
                Yours&#44;<lb/>
                S. C. Brace.<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">At the Merc. Liby. 10th St</hi>.<lb/></p>
            </body>
